==English==

===Etymology===
Prefix "neo-" (from greek 'neos'= "new") and "tropical" (from greek 'tropikos', referring to where the length of the day equals that of the night)

===Adjective===
# Occurring in tropical America, i.e. the tropics of "the new world". Used in biology, pertaining to area of geographical occurrence. 

